= Contributing to RAG

== Licensing your work to us

When you open a pull request, you agree to provide your work under the link:LICENSE.asc[project license].
If your changes are merged, they will be distributed under the same license.

== Signaling an Issue

Search for similar issues before creating a new issue.

Also, if this issue has been spotted in the CLI/TUI, cross-check that the issue is present with the current dependency set.
The issue may have already been corrected in the source files, but not yet released.

== Small Corrections

Errata, clarifications, and small fixes are welcome if they improve correctness or usability.
You can also open an issue so that we can discuss how or if the issue needs to be addressed.

If you've never done this before, the https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/quickstart/github-flow[flow guide] might be useful.

== Large Rewrites

Open an issue for discussion before you start.
Large rewrites are subjective and should be scoped to clear, measurable improvements.
If a change affects behavior, include tests or update existing ones.

== Figures

This project does not currently include a figure generation pipeline.
If you add diagrams, include the source files and document how to regenerate them.

== Translations

If you want to contribute translations, take a look at link:TRANSLATING.md[TRANSLATING.md].
